Welcome to February's Turing-Roche newsletter! Here you can find what's new in the Turing-Roche strategic partnership and opportunities, events and news from both the Alan Turing Institute, Roche and the wider community.

Our [five year partnership](https://eur01.safelinks.protection.outlook.com/?url=http%3A%2F%2Felink.turing.ac.uk%2Fc%2F7%%2FBBFlnuJIp3x9yknfvqCFhw&data=05%7C01%7Cvhellon%40turing.ac.uk%7C3ad576710c1c4db606ed08db1409a767%7C4395f4a7e4554f958a9f1fbaef6384f9%7C0%7C0%7C638125803936327095%7CUnknown%7CTWFpbGZsb3d8eyJWIjoiMC4wLjAwMDAiLCJQIjoiV2luMzIiLCJBTiI6Ik1haWwiLCJXVCI6Mn0%3D%7C3000%7C%7C%7C&sdata=EijnRzQMXvV6MwNspuyCMQtnsWKoyAgIXh9HxWdP2w4%3D&reserved=0) was set up officially in June 2021 following a successful [Data Study Group](https://eur01.safelinks.protection.outlook.com/?url=http%3A%2F%2Felink.turing.ac.uk%2Fc%2F7%%2FkSfBuWTuUPOb2Lp7JRONRg&data=05%7C01%7Cvhellon%40turing.ac.uk%7C3ad576710c1c4db606ed08db1409a767%7C4395f4a7e4554f958a9f1fbaef6384f9%7C0%7C0%7C638125803936327095%7CUnknown%7CTWFpbGZsb3d8eyJWIjoiMC4wLjAwMDAiLCJQIjoiV2luMzIiLCJBTiI6Ik1haWwiLCJXVCI6Mn0%3D%7C3000%7C%7C%7C&sdata=XfqJjcanuApKTN%2BoR3g%2FzXRlZgNPU9HsR0QCyD%2Fi1rg%3D&reserved=0) and a 12 week research project on lung cancer treatment. Our 'North Star' is **to enable the generation of insights to better understand patient and disease heterogeneity and its relevance to clinical outcomes at an unprecedented level of precision in order to improve clinical care.**

We will be covering multiple activities over the five years to work towards our North Star, as well as building strong connections and collaborations between the Alan Turing Institute, Roche and the wider community.

If you have anything you'd like featured in a future newsletter then please get in touch with Vicky Hellon, Community Manager for the partnership at <vhellon@turing.ac.uk>

If you would like to share this newsletter with relevant colleagues please direct them to sign-up [here](https://eur01.safelinks.protection.outlook.com/?url=http%3A%2F%2Felink.turing.ac.uk%2Fc%2F7%%2FOo-QzV7fNCvHBoUhmb_RUA&data=05%7C01%7Cvhellon%40turing.ac.uk%7C3ad576710c1c4db606ed08db1409a767%7C4395f4a7e4554f958a9f1fbaef6384f9%7C0%7C0%7C638125803936483341%7CUnknown%7CTWFpbGZsb3d8eyJWIjoiMC4wLjAwMDAiLCJQIjoiV2luMzIiLCJBTiI6Ik1haWwiLCJXVCI6Mn0%3D%7C3000%7C%7C%7C&sdata=hwUs9Xak9F0OCPyWHSUHUpFp3MV7DRa7AGZsH5Teq3Q%3D&reserved=0).

### First Partnership Paper Published: Learning from data with Structured Missingness 

We're really excited that the first partnership paper has been published in [Nature Machine Intelligence](https://eur01.safelinks.protection.outlook.com/?url=http%3A%2F%2Felink.turing.ac.uk%2Fc%2F7%%2FNIyicP5t9KTXMVuZnPYKgA&data=05%7C01%7Cvhellon%40turing.ac.uk%7C3ad576710c1c4db606ed08db1409a767%7C4395f4a7e4554f958a9f1fbaef6384f9%7C0%7C0%7C638125803936483341%7CUnknown%7CTWFpbGZsb3d8eyJWIjoiMC4wLjAwMDAiLCJQIjoiV2luMzIiLCJBTiI6Ik1haWwiLCJXVCI6Mn0%3D%7C3000%7C%7C%7C&sdata=eRoQ02fx6dtXAUOtcKlUZZumyb3ziA2%2FuzPFg6GX9ow%3D&reserved=0). The paper explores a series of grand challenges and solutions to Structured Missingness in data, which is the partnership's first research theme. We believe Structured Missingness is a fundamental challenge to machine learning at scale and that alongside creating tools to mitigate it, gaining a more holistic understanding of it could convey important information about the data itself, leading to significant advances in healthcare and beyond. You can find out more [here](https://eur01.safelinks.protection.outlook.com/?url=http%3A%2F%2Felink.turing.ac.uk%2Fc%2F7%%2FbkIDMXca3m108lUWotGx4w&data=05%7C01%7Cvhellon%40turing.ac.uk%7C3ad576710c1c4db606ed08db1409a767%7C4395f4a7e4554f958a9f1fbaef6384f9%7C0%7C0%7C638125803936483341%7CUnknown%7CTWFpbGZsb3d8eyJWIjoiMC4wLjAwMDAiLCJQIjoiV2luMzIiLCJBTiI6Ik1haWwiLCJXVCI6Mn0%3D%7C3000%7C%7C%7C&sdata=6GGvg7tw87YPO9gKxU%2FSs%2B%2BqMqpalLKAfCqq50gM1uA%3D&reserved=0) and we'd love to hear your thoughts on the paper through our [Slack Workspace](https://eur01.safelinks.protection.outlook.com/?url=http%3A%2F%2Felink.turing.ac.uk%2Fc%2F7%%2FtPuZMNrLcesA3JpMc2JuYg&data=05%7C01%7Cvhellon%40turing.ac.uk%7C3ad576710c1c4db606ed08db1409a767%7C4395f4a7e4554f958a9f1fbaef6384f9%7C0%7C0%7C638125803936483341%7CUnknown%7CTWFpbGZsb3d8eyJWIjoiMC4wLjAwMDAiLCJQIjoiV2luMzIiLCJBTiI6Ik1haWwiLCJXVCI6Mn0%3D%7C3000%7C%7C%7C&sdata=OmbjlLEnFafsBZdmu91xJZh%2Fe0QXpqPtClioFEFmEkM%3D&reserved=0).

### Knowledge Share Series Event: Digital Health

**27 February 2023**

Join us for our [partnership knowledge share series](https://eur01.safelinks.protection.outlook.com/?url=http%3A%2F%2Felink.turing.ac.uk%2Fc%2F7%%2FFuEKnnktepEfMVuQMAAnQA&data=05%7C01%7Cvhellon%40turing.ac.uk%7C3ad576710c1c4db606ed08db1409a767%7C4395f4a7e4554f958a9f1fbaef6384f9%7C0%7C0%7C638125803936483341%7CUnknown%7CTWFpbGZsb3d8eyJWIjoiMC4wLjAwMDAiLCJQIjoiV2luMzIiLCJBTiI6Ik1haWwiLCJXVCI6Mn0%3D%7C3000%7C%7C%7C&sdata=qAlhikhUIklQWNoDGDiYFPTiPNqsiiaXJ4nXzadYF3Q%3D&reserved=0). Our aim is to bring together members of the Turing and Roche networks and the wider scientific community to share different academic and industry perspectives on areas related to patient/treatment heterogeneity and data science more generally.

February's event is on the 27th and this month our theme will be Digital Health. We'll be exploring how the increasing amount of collected 'footprint' data can be used to develop healthcare research and products and considerations around this.

We'll be hearing from Elizabeth Dolan, PhD Student at University of Nottingham's Digital Economy Horizon Centre of Doctoral Training and N/LAB research centre for the use of big data and machine learning and Jian Dai, Expert Data Scientist and Ophthalmology Imaging R&D Lead, Data Science Capability Lead and Yajing Zhu, Principal Data Scientist and Neuroscience Network Lead, both at Roche. You can register [here](https://eur01.safelinks.protection.outlook.com/?url=http%3A%2F%2Felink.turing.ac.uk%2Fc%2F7%%2FF5aglvWo7AQLzZ9AZmSvaw&data=05%7C01%7Cvhellon%40turing.ac.uk%7C3ad576710c1c4db606ed08db1409a767%7C4395f4a7e4554f958a9f1fbaef6384f9%7C0%7C0%7C638125803936483341%7CUnknown%7CTWFpbGZsb3d8eyJWIjoiMC4wLjAwMDAiLCJQIjoiV2luMzIiLCJBTiI6Ik1haWwiLCJXVCI6Mn0%3D%7C3000%7C%7C%7C&sdata=%2B19DW%2F5thwxzcrsFUej%2FRe04kBNDMmRJMMa3V%2BDiN18%3D&reserved=0).

You can catch-up on previous recordings of our events at our [YouTube channel](https://eur01.safelinks.protection.outlook.com/?url=http%3A%2F%2Felink.turing.ac.uk%2Fc%2F7%%2Fla6_Mvy1fmBJFoPw9vgiiA&data=05%7C01%7Cvhellon%40turing.ac.uk%7C3ad576710c1c4db606ed08db1409a767%7C4395f4a7e4554f958a9f1fbaef6384f9%7C0%7C0%7C638125803936483341%7CUnknown%7CTWFpbGZsb3d8eyJWIjoiMC4wLjAwMDAiLCJQIjoiV2luMzIiLCJBTiI6Ik1haWwiLCJXVCI6Mn0%3D%7C3000%7C%7C%7C&sdata=SM71l0CwtcKMS2HKU1T7Wc8QpSfcEVzN34WzS9Jz0KM%3D&reserved=0). ### Machine learning and AI in biological science, drug discovery and medicine

**1 March 2023**

The Royal Society are hosting a hybrid one day conference to bring together stakeholders from industry and academia to explore advances in machine learning and artificial intelligence for biological research, drug discovery and medicine. Three sessions around biology, chemistry and medicine will include talks on machine learning for target discovery and 'omic technologies, AI-based chemoinformatics, and computational clinical trial design, as well as the classical prediction of protein folding, followed by a keynote address from Dr Demis Hassabis from DeepMind. Registration [here](https://eur01.safelinks.protection.outlook.com/?url=http%3A%2F%2Felink.turing.ac.uk%2Fc%2F7%%2FTVdOVjvLUR5dcIgFXw3Mog&data=05%7C01%7Cvhellon%40turing.ac.uk%7C3ad576710c1c4db606ed08db1409a767%7C4395f4a7e4554f958a9f1fbaef6384f9%7C0%7C0%7C638125803936639642%7CUnknown%7CTWFpbGZsb3d8eyJWIjoiMC4wLjAwMDAiLCJQIjoiV2luMzIiLCJBTiI6Ik1haWwiLCJXVCI6Mn0%3D%7C3000%7C%7C%7C&sdata=ix46DzX%2FL46NE0QT3OnX8YCIS66bGxNyf3BvYMtcXNw%3D&reserved=0).

### University of Birmingham and Health Data Research UK (HDR UK)- Health Data Immersion Week: Working with Real World Data 

**Deadline for applications: 26 February 2023**

**Immersion Week: 27-31 March 2023**

Working with University Hospitals Birmingham, through the HDR UK supported PIONEER Data Hub, this course will give participants from across the UK an insight into the potential and challenges of real-world health data, and practical experience of working with health data. It will highlight the significant data engineering efforts that underlie the provision of research-ready data and the use of a modern secure computing environment that is the emerging standard for accessing UK health data. The course will be in-person and you can apply [here](https://eur01.safelinks.protection.outlook.com/?url=http%3A%2F%2Felink.turing.ac.uk%2Fc%2F7%_X2NsZGVlPWpLVmtwY2M4X3FKMjB3RFNTbnZwam04WFduUW44RFVhUjNLMHd6M3JfRWItTkw2aklYVlZkc0k3TWRMUmh4WngmcmVjaXBpZW50aWQ9Y29udGFjdC00ODgwYThjMzkyM2NlYzExOGM2MjAwMjI0ODQzNGZlYi00M2ZhNGIyNTA0MjA0MmJhYjhkMmIzNzc3OWNlZTU2YSZlc2lkPWVlZjJhZDU1LTk5YTgtZWQxMS1hYWQxLTAwMjI0ODA3ZThiMyJ9%2F7ZtKmc83FduexBWLi1mzSw&data=05%7C01%7Cvhellon%40turing.ac.uk%7C3ad576710c1c4db606ed08db1409a767%7C4395f4a7e4554f958a9f1fbaef6384f9%7C0%7C0%7C638125803936639642%7CUnknown%7CTWFpbGZsb3d8eyJWIjoiMC4wLjAwMDAiLCJQIjoiV2luMzIiLCJBTiI6Ik1haWwiLCJXVCI6Mn0%3D%7C3000%7C%7C%7C&sdata=B1Ej06op4JvGDeGKgYmF%2FGAjJitodALDPgAKUt5aI5U%3D&reserved=0).

## Publication of the Month

![](https://file-eu.clickdimensions.com/turingacuk-ap7zg/files/patrick-tomasso-oaqk7qqnh_c-unsplash2.jpg)

**Fair Conformal Predictors for Applications in Medical Imaging**

Apart from our amazing partnership publication out (see above!) we also wanted to highlight [this paper](https://eur01.safelinks.protection.outlook.com/?url=http%3A%2F%2Felink.turing.ac.uk%2Fc%2F7%%2Fc0Xq22NRp2l63Tv82m2hyg&data=05%7C01%7Cvhellon%40turing.ac.uk%7C3ad576710c1c4db606ed08db1409a767%7C4395f4a7e4554f958a9f1fbaef6384f9%7C0%7C0%7C638125803936795892%7CUnknown%7CTWFpbGZsb3d8eyJWIjoiMC4wLjAwMDAiLCJQIjoiV2luMzIiLCJBTiI6Ik1haWwiLCJXVCI6Mn0%3D%7C3000%7C%7C%7C&sdata=hV29twDEN3%2F1iL23wxydrMCk3qSH%2FaZAELvoeAySRvU%3D&reserved=0) for our February publication of the month. Published in the Proceedings of the AAAI Conference on Artificial Intelligence, this paper from Charles Lu (Athinoula A. Martinos Center for Biomedical Imaging) and colleagues presents how conformal predictions can be used to quantify uncertainty of machine learning models for medical imaging applications. The aim is to increase transparency and fairness of 'black box' deep models for personalised healthcare and precision medicine, and 'conformal learning' has strong potential to facilitate this.
